From 0035aaaa11112222333344445555666677778888 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Henry AI <henry.ai@example.com>
Date: Thu, 9 Jul 2026 18:00:00 +0800
Subject: [PATCH] phy: rockchip: balance RK3399 PCIe logical PHY runtime PM

Live 0034 validation removed repeated PCIe PHY underflow from the host retry
loop, but each deferred bring-up still emitted one runtime-PM underflow per
logical RK3399 PCIe PHY child before link training started.

The generic PHY core returns -ENOTSUPP from phy_pm_runtime_get_sync() when a
child PHY device has runtime PM disabled, but phy_init()/phy_exit() still call
the async runtime-PM put path afterwards.  For the RK3399 PCIe PHY provider the
four child PHYs are logical lanes backed by one shared reset/refclk/PLL block,
and the provider already protects that hardware with init_cnt/pwr_cnt and has
no runtime-PM callbacks.

Enable no-callback runtime PM on each logical child after devm_phy_create().
This keeps the generic PHY core get/put accounting balanced while preserving
the provider's explicit refclk/reset handling.  Keep the 0034 host retry policy
that avoids PHY deinit between Gen1 training attempts.

Signed-off-by: Henry AI <henry.ai@example.com>
---
diff --git a/drivers/phy/rockchip/phy-rockchip-pcie.c b/drivers/phy/rockchip/phy-rockchip-pcie.c
index 8cd03f1..e75e9c4 100644
--- a/drivers/phy/rockchip/phy-rockchip-pcie.c
+++ b/drivers/phy/rockchip/phy-rockchip-pcie.c
@@ -15,6 +15,7 @@
 #include <linux/of.h>
 #include <linux/phy/phy.h>
 #include <linux/platform_device.h>
+#include <linux/pm_runtime.h>
 #include <linux/property.h>
 #include <linux/regmap.h>
 #include <linux/reset.h>
@@ -315,14 +316,16 @@ static int rockchip_pcie_phy_probe(struct platform_device *pdev)
 		rk_phy->phys[i].index = i;
 		/*
 		 * RK3399 exposes four logical PHY lanes backed by one shared legacy
-		 * PCIe PHY/reset block.  The provider has no runtime-PM callbacks and
-		 * handles refclk/reset explicitly in its init/power ops.  Keeping the
-		 * generic per-child PHY runtime-PM accounting enabled can underflow
-		 * during host link-training retry/exit sequences, which hides the real
-		 * LTSSM state we need to debug.  Disable the child accounting and rely
-		 * on the driver's existing init_cnt/pwr_cnt serialization.
+		 * PCIe PHY/reset block.  The provider handles refclk/reset explicitly
+		 * in its init/power ops and has no runtime-PM callbacks.  However the
+		 * generic PHY core unconditionally does a runtime-PM put after init/exit,
+		 * even when get_sync() returned -ENOTSUPP for a disabled child device.
+		 * Enable no-callback runtime PM on each logical child so generic PHY
+		 * get/put accounting stays balanced while the provider's init_cnt/pwr_cnt
+		 * remain the real shared-hardware guards.
 		 */
-		pm_runtime_disable(&rk_phy->phys[i].phy->dev);
+		pm_runtime_enable(&rk_phy->phys[i].phy->dev);
+		pm_runtime_no_callbacks(&rk_phy->phys[i].phy->dev);
 		phy_set_drvdata(rk_phy->phys[i].phy, &rk_phy->phys[i]);
 	}
 
